# Keep shell scripts and git hooks LF-only so they run under bash/sh on every
# platform. A CRLF `.sh` (or hook) checked out on Windows fails with
# `bad interpreter: /bin/bash^M` / `\r: command not found` — which would brick
# `make hook-install` and every host-run script the moment a Windows contributor
# clones. Everything else runs in Docker, but hooks and scripts run on the host.
# Scoped narrowly (not a blanket `* text=auto`) to avoid renormalizing the tree.
*.sh        text eol=lf
.githooks/* text eol=lf
